10. Mutual Termination for Patent Action
---------------------------------------

10.1. Anti-Patent Agreements

No Contributor may bring any patent claim against any other Contributor, or against any Recipient, for any infringement or alleged infringement based on that Contributor's making, using, selling, offering for sale, having made, importing, exporting, using, reproducing, making available, propagating, preparing, displaying, performing, or distributing its Contributions, either on an unmodified basis, with Modifications, or as part of a Larger Work.

10.2. Defensive Termination

If You initiate litigation against any entity by asserting a patent infringement claim (excluding declaratory judgment actions, counter-claims, and cross-claims) alleging that a Contribution by any Contributor directly or indirectly infringes any patent, then the rights granted to You by any and all Contributors under Sections 2.1 and/or 2.2 of this License shall terminate as of the date such litigation is filed.

10.3. Defensive Termination for Support Providers

If You, as a Support Provider, initiate litigation against any entity by asserting a patent infringement claim (excluding declaratory judgment actions, counter-claims, and cross-claims) alleging that a Contribution by any Contributor directly or indirectly infringes any patent, then You must stop all distributions of Covered Software to the extent that any of Your distributions are made under a version of this License that includes the provisions of Section 10.3. If You make such distributions under other licenses, then You must stop all distributions that are made under the terms of any version of this License that includes the provisions of Section 10.3, or that are derived from or based on such a version of this License.

10.4. Acceleration of Definitions and Assimilation Provisions

If the rights granted to You under Sections 2.1 and/or 2.2 of this License terminate under this Section 10, then all of Your patent licenses granted under such Sections 2.1 and 2.2 terminate. Further, You agree to grant and do hereby grant to each Contributor whose rights under Sections 2.1 and/or 2.2 terminate, an irrevocable, non-exclusive, royalty-free, fully-paid, perpetual, worldwide patent license, under all Patent Claims owned by You and licensed to such Contributor by You as of the date such termination occurs, to make, have made, use, sell, offer for sale, import, export, or otherwise dispose of, and to sublicense (directly or indirectly) the Covered Software under this License, the License or any version of this License published by the Mozilla Foundation, or under any subsequent version of this License. If You create or use a Modifications, then the irrevocable patent license for such Modifications granted under this Section 10.4 shall apply.

